Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *AI Engineer* role with *Bain Capital Special Situations*. I bring over three years of professional experience building production-grade AI agents, LLM-powered pipelines, and workflow automation systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade AI solutions that directly reflect the technical depth and experimentation mindset this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an MCP AI interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, prompt engineering, and safe execution across a distributed surface. I designed a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph for scalable Agentic AI workflows, and implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks — reducing end-to-end LLM latency by 60% and API costs by 50% through targeted concurrency optimizations. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I built a RAG-based support chatbot with a PostgreSQL vector database that reduced ticket resolution time by 20%, and designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that maintained reliable API connections and data pipelines across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO. I also developed workflow automation using AWS Step Functions to orchestrate long-running data import jobs — the kind of practical, data-heavy automation work central to streamlining investment processes from sourcing to portfolio analytics. Together, these roles have prepared me to build and deploy AI solutions that improve decision-making efficiency and drive measurable impact across investment and operational teams.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the experimental discipline and collaborative culture Bain Capital values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster, managing the full model lifecycle from data preparation through inference optimization with vLLM and Hugging Face deployment. Beyond building systems, I led workshops on GPU programming and building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph for 50+ students — directly mirroring the role of an internal AI champion who trains the team on new capabilities and ensures adoption of the most useful tools and workflows. This experience shaped me into an engineer who prototypes fast, evaluates honestly, and communicates complex AI concepts clearly to non-technical stakeholders.


I have always been passionate about creating lasting impact through rigorous problem-solving and integrity, and I envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Bain Capital's mission to create lasting value for investors, businesses, and the communities they serve. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

